=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
חרה / chârâh / khaw-raw'

=== Etymology ===

A primitive root (compare {{HH|2787}}); 
=== Verb ===
to glow or grow warm; figuratively (usually) to blaze up, of anger, zeal, jealousy: - be angry, burn, be displeased, X earnestly, fret self, grieve, be (wax) hot, be incensed, kindle, X very, be wroth. See H8474.

